<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFB06A0FF82497831751B9F2" blockId="75.[2006,2602,277,704]" pageId="75" pageNumber="833">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFB06A0FF82497831684BAC9" bold="true" box="[2008,2180,474,507]" pageId="75" pageNumber="833">Distribution.</emphasis>
W &amp; C Africa, from 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFB06A0FF61897831623B911" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="75" pageNumber="833">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
E through 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFB06A0FF71C945B173CB911" box="[2272,2364,514,547]" name="Ghana" pageId="75" pageNumber="833">Ghana</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFB06A0FF669945B17FAB911" box="[2453,2554,514,547]" name="Nigeria" pageId="75" pageNumber="833">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFB06A0FF8249470166AB978" box="[2008,2154,553,586]" name="Cameroon" pageId="75" pageNumber="833">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFB06A0FF74F947017B1B978" box="[2227,2481,553,586]" name="Equatorial Guinea" pageId="75" pageNumber="833">Equatorial Guinea</collectingCountry>
(including Bioko I), with scattered records from S 
